# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# PREFERRED CITATION (The research paper)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
preferred-citation:
  type: article
  title: "Efficient Strategies for Constructing Robust Machine Learning Potentials"
  abstract: "Machine Learning Interatomic Potentials, MLIPs, hold the key for the design of materials with tailored properties. Although a rigorous and robust conceptual framework has been built for these methodologies leading to the first foundational models the accuracy and adaptability to particular applications needs to be streamlined. Here we have developed a systematic approach based on comprehensive database generation and descriptor-driven intelligent phase space exploration via active learning to accelerate the rate of learning from new structures thus minimizing the cost of active learning strategies. Our work paves the way to the development of unbiased active learning strategies to tailor foundational MLP models to practical applications."

